      "narrative": "Hathor mainnet launched on 3 January 2020 and added SHA-256d merge-mining later that year.\n\nHathor merge-mining is not Bitcoin-only. Early public HathorMM coverage named Bitcoin Cash, Bitcoin SV, and DigiByte parents.[^2] F2Pool later listed HTR as a BTC-merged coin.[^4]\n\nFor this monitor, Hathor is a high-frequency SHA-256d witness with an important caveat: every reconstructed parent header must still be filtered to decide whether it is really a Bitcoin parent."
